"Validate Agent Team is in Session","message":["%script","","-- Validate Agent Team in Session","SELECT DBMS_CLOUD_AI_AGENT.GET_TEAM FROM DUAL;"],"enabled":true,"result":{"startTime":1776967055731,"interpreter":"script.medium","endTime":1776967056163,"results":[{"message":"\nGET_TEAM                               \n\"ISMAIL\".\"OPS_ISSUES_SOLUTION_TEAM\"    \n\n\n---------------------------\n","type":"TEXT"}],"taskStatus":"SUCCESS","forms":"[]","status":"SUCCESS"},"sizeX":0,"hideCode":false,"width":12,"hideResult":false,"dynamicFormParams":"{}","row":0,"hasTitle":true,"hideVizConfig":false,"hideGutter":true,"relations":[],"forms":"[]"},{"col":0,"visualizationConfig":"[{\"raw\":{\"lastColumns\":[\"RESPONSE\"],\"version\":1}}]","hideInIFrame":false,"selectedVisualization":"raw","title":"Interact with Agent Team","message":["%sql","","-- Initiate Agent","select ai agent fetch and analyze the logs after 2025-03-20;"],"enabled":true,"result":{"startTime":1776967063217,"interpreter":"sql.medium","endTime":1776967099489,"results":[{"message":"RESPONSE\nEmail sent successfully to DB Operations Team with the log analysis report for logs after 2025-03-20.\n","type":"TABLE"}],"taskStatus":"SUCCESS","forms":"[]","status":"SUCCESS"},"sizeX":0,"hideCode":false,"width":12,"hideResult":false,"dynamicFormParams":"{}","row":0,"hasTitle":true,"hideVizConfig":false,"hideGutter":true,"relations":[],"forms":"[]"},{"col":0,"visualizationConfig":null,"hideInIFrame":false,"selectedVisualization":"table","title":"View Tool History","message":["%sql","","-- View the tool history","SELECT ","    * ","FROM ","    USER_AI_AGENT_TOOL_HISTORY","ORDER BY","    START_DATE DESC"],"enabled":true,"result":{"startTime":1776967153683,"interpreter":"sql.medium","endTime":1776967154085,"results":[{"message":"INVOCATION_ID\tTEAM_EXEC_ID\tTASK_ORDER\tTOOL_NAME\tAGENT_NAME\tTASK_NAME\tSTART_DATE\tEND_DATE\tINPUT\tOUTPUT\tTOOL_OUTPUT\n234\t5025368E-C5BE-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\t2\tLOG_REPORT_EMAIL_TOOL\tEMAIL_LOG_REPORT_AGENT\tEMAIL_LOGS_REPORT_TASK\t2026-04-23 17:58:16.562331 +0:00\t2026-04-23 17:58:17.210914 +0:00\t{\"TOOL_NAME\":\"LOG_REPORT_EMAIL_TOOL\",\"EMAIL_SUBJECT\":\"Database Log Analysis Report - Logs after 2025-03-20\",\"EMAIL_BODY\":\"Hi DB Operations Team,\\n\\n# Database Operations Team Report: Log Analysis Post 2025-03-20\\n\\n## Executive Summary\\n- **Date Range Analyzed**: Logs after 2025-03-20.\\n- **Key Events**: 3 log entries identified.\\n  1. **ERROR (ID: dbfailover102)**: Primary DB unreachable, failover initiated.\\n  2. **INFO (ID: dbswitchover215)**: Switchover sync restored, scheduled switchover.\\n  3. **INFO (ID: dbfailover102)**: Failover completed, standby promoted with 33s downtime.\\n- **Overall Assessment**: An unplanned failover occurred due to primary DB outage, resolved quickly (33s downtime). This was followed by a planned switchover. No ongoing issues apparent; system stability restored.\\n\\n## Issue Analysis\\n- **Root Cause**: Primary database became unreachable (likely due to hardware failure, network partition, or resource exhaustion\u2014further investigation needed).\\n- **Impact**:\\n  - Minimal downtime (33 seconds), indicating effective high-availability setup.\\n  - Automatic failover to standby succeeded.\\n  - Subsequent planned switchover suggests proactive management to restore optimal configuration.\\n- **Timeline**:\\n  1. Detection of primary failure ? Immediate failover initiation.\\n  2. Failover completion and promotion of standby.\\n  3. Sync restoration and scheduled switchover (possibly to rebalance or prepare for maintenance).\\n- **Severity**: Medium (brief outage, auto-resolved). No data loss indicated.\\n- **Patterns**: Isolated incident; no recurring errors in provided logs.\\n\\n## Possible Solutions & Recommendations\\n1. **Immediate Actions**:\\n   - Review primary DB diagnostics (e.g., alert logs, OS metrics) around failover timestamp to pinpoint failure cause (CPU/memory spike, disk I/O, network?).\\n   - Validate current primary (post-switchover) health: Run health checks, replication lag queries.\\n\\n2. **Preventive Measures**:\\n   - **Monitoring Enhancements**: Implement proactive alerts for primary DB metrics (e.g., CPU >80%, connection pool exhaustion) using tools like Oracle Enterprise Manager or Prometheus.\\n   - **Root Cause Investigation**: \\n     - Check hardware/network logs.\\n     - Test failover manually in staging to benchmark response time.\\n   - **Configuration Tuning**:\\n     | Area | Recommendation | Expected Benefit |\\n     |------|----------------|------------------|\\n     | Fast-Start Failover | Ensure `dg_broker_start=TRUE` and tune thresholds | Faster detection (<10s). |\\n     | Replication | Verify `log_archive_dest` sync; reduce lag | Minimize data loss risk. |\\n     | Resource Limits | Set DB resource manager plans | Prevent overload-induced failures. |\\n\\n3. **Long-Term Improvements**:\\n   - Schedule regular switchover drills (quarterly).\\n   - Upgrade to latest Data Guard patches if not current.\\n   - Consider multi-region standby for higher resilience.\\n   - Automate post-failover reports via scripts.\\n\\n## Next Steps\\n- Assign RCA ticket for primary failure (target: 48 hours).\\n- Monitor for 24-48 hours post-report.\\n- Contact if additional logs or metrics needed.\\n\\nReport generated by OPS_MANAGER_AGENT. No ongoing issues; system nominal.\\n\\nMany thanks,\\nIssy and Thomas\"}\t{\"status\":\"success\",\"result\":\"{\\\"status\\\":\\\"success\\\",\\\"message\\\":\\\"Email sent successfully to ismail.s.syed@oracle.com\\\"}\"}\tCLOB\n233\t5025368E-C5BE-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\t0\tLOG_FETCHER_TOOL\tDATA_ENGINEER_AGENT\tFETCH_LOGS_TASK\t2026-04-23 17:57:51.125733 +0:00\t2026-04-23 17:57:51.178728 +0:00\t{\"SINCE_DATE\": \"2025-03-20\"}\t{\"status\":\"success\",\"result\":\"[\\\"INFO: Database Cluster: Failover completed successfully. Standby promoted to primary. Downtime duration: 33 seconds. Correlation ID: dbfailover102.\\\",\\\"INFO: Switchover Process: Synchronization restored. Performing scheduled switchover. Correlation ID: dbswitchover215.\\\",\\\"ERROR: Database Cluster: Primary database unreachable, initiating failover to standby. Correlation ID: dbfailover102.\\\"]\"}\tCLOB\n231\t50249D1C-B6C0-6781-E063-6A13000AF668\t0\tUPDATE_ORDER_STATUS_TOOL\tCUSTOMER_RETURN_AGENT\tHANDLE_PRODUCT_RETURN_TASK\t2026-04-23 17:18:13.481872 +0:00\t2026-04-23 17:18:13.642537 +0:00\t{\"P_CUSTOMER_NAME\": \"Bob Martinez\", \"P_ORDER_NUMBER\": \"7820\", \"P_STATUS\": \"replaced\"}\t{\"status\":\"success\",\"result\":\"'Update successful.'\"}\tCLOB\n","type":"TABLE"}],"taskStatus":"SUCCESS","forms":"[]","status":"SUCCESS"},"sizeX":0,"hideCode":false,"width":12,"hideResult":false,"dynamicFormParams":"{}","row":0,"hasTitle":true,"hideVizConfig":false,"hideGutter":true,"relations":[],"forms":"[]"},{"col":0,"visualizationConfig":null,"hideInIFrame":false,"selectedVisualization":"table","title":"View Task History","message":["%sql","","-- View the task history","SELECT","    * ","FROM","    USER_AI_AGENT_TASK_HISTORY","ORDER BY ","    START_DATE DESC"],"enabled":true,"result":{"startTime":1776967156727,"interpreter":"sql.medium","endTime":1776967157091,"results":[{"message":"TEAM_EXEC_ID\tTEAM_NAME\tTASK_ORDER\tAGENT_NAME\tTASK_NAME\tCONVERSATION_PARAMS\tINPUT\tRESULT\tSTATE\tSTART_DATE\tEND_DATE\n5025368E-C5BE-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\tOPS_ISSUES_SOLUTION_TEAM\t2\tEMAIL_LOG_REPORT_AGENT\tEMAIL_LOGS_REPORT_TASK\t{\"conversation_id\":\"5025368E-C5C1-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\"}\tfetch and analyze the logs after 2025-03-20\tEmail sent successfully to DB Operations Team with the log analysis report for logs after 2025-03-20.\tSUCCEEDED\t2026-04-23 17:58:04.660306 +0:00\t2026-04-23 17:58:19.191394 +0:00\n5025368E-C5BE-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\tOPS_ISSUES_SOLUTION_TEAM\t1\tOPS_MANAGER_AGENT\tANALYZE_LOGS_TASK\t{\"conversation_id\":\"5025368E-C5C0-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\"}\tfetch and analyze the logs after 2025-03-20\t# Database Operations Team Report: Log Analysis Post 2025-03-20  ## Executive Summary - **Date Range Analyzed**: Logs after 2025-03-20. - **Key Events**: 3 log entries identified.   1. **ERROR (ID: dbfailover102)**: Primary DB unreachable, failover initiated.   2. **INFO (ID: dbswitchover215)**: Switchover sync restored, scheduled switchover.   3. **INFO (ID: dbfailover102)**: Failover completed, standby promoted with 33s downtime. - **Overall Assessment**: An unplanned failover occurred due to primary DB outage, resolved quickly (33s downtime). This was followed by a planned switchover. No ongoing issues apparent; system stability restored.  ## Issue Analysis - **Root Cause**: Primary database became unreachable (likely due to hardware failure, network partition, or resource exhaustion\u2014further investigation needed). - **Impact**:   - Minimal downtime (33 seconds), indicating effective high-availability setup.   - Automatic failover to standby succeeded.   - Subsequent planned switchover suggests proactive management to restore optimal configuration. - **Timeline**:   1. Detection of primary failure ? Immediate failover initiation.   2. Failover completion and promotion of standby.   3. Sync restoration and scheduled switchover (possibly to rebalance or prepare for maintenance). - **Severity**: Medium (brief outage, auto-resolved). No data loss indicated. - **Patterns**: Isolated incident; no recurring errors in provided logs.  ## Possible Solutions & Recommendations 1. **Immediate Actions**:    - Review primary DB diagnostics (e.g., alert logs, OS metrics) around failover timestamp to pinpoint failure cause (CPU/memory spike, disk I/O, network?).    - Validate current primary (post-switchover) health: Run health checks, replication lag queries.  2. **Preventive Measures**:    - **Monitoring Enhancements**: Implement proactive alerts for primary DB metrics (e.g., CPU >80%, connection pool exhaustion) using tools like Oracle Enterprise Manager or Prometheus.    - **Root Cause Investigation**:       - Check hardware/network logs.      - Test failover manually in staging to benchmark response time.    - **Configuration Tuning**:      | Area | Recommendation | Expected Benefit |      |------|----------------|------------------|      | Fast-Start Failover | Ensure `dg_broker_start=TRUE` and tune thresholds | Faster detection (<10s). |      | Replication | Verify `log_archive_dest` sync; reduce lag | Minimize data loss risk. |      | Resource Limits | Set DB resource manager plans | Prevent overload-induced failures. |  3. **Long-Term Improvements**:    - Schedule regular switchover drills (quarterly).    - Upgrade to latest Data Guard patches if not current.    - Consider multi-region standby for higher resilience.    - Automate post-failover reports via scripts.  ## Next Steps - Assign RCA ticket for primary failure (target: 48 hours). - Monitor for 24-48 hours post-report. - Contact if additional logs or metrics needed.  Report generated by OPS_MANAGER_AGENT. No ongoing issues; system nominal.\tSUCCEEDED\t2026-04-23 17:57:54.440815 +0:00\t2026-04-23 17:58:04.283384 +0:00\n5025368E-C5BE-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\tOPS_ISSUES_SOLUTION_TEAM\t0\tDATA_ENGINEER_AGENT\tFETCH_LOGS_TASK\t{\"conversation_id\":\"5025368E-C5BF-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\"}\tfetch and analyze the logs after 2025-03-20\tFetched 3 log entries after 2025-03-20. Analysis: 1. ERROR - Primary DB unreachable, failover initiated (ID: dbfailover102). 2. INFO - Switchover sync restored, scheduled switchover (ID: dbswitchover215). 3. INFO - Failover completed, standby promoted, 33s downtime (ID: dbfailover102). Overall: Unplanned failover due to outage, quickly resolved; followed by planned switchover. No ongoing issues apparent.\tSUCCEEDED\t2026-04-23 17:57:44.883985 +0:00\t2026-04-23 17:57:54.010705 +0:00\n50249D1C-B6C0-6781-E063-6A13000AF668\tRETURN_AGENCY_TEAM\t0\tCUSTOMER_RETURN_AGENT\tHANDLE_PRODUCT_RETURN_TASK\t{\"conversation_id\":\"50249D1C-B6C1-6781-E063-6A13000AF668\"}\tI want to return a smartphone case\tYou're welcome, Bob. It was a pleasure assisting you with the return and replacement of your smartphone case. Have a great day!\tSUCCEEDED\t2026-04-23 17:17:30.639443 +0:00\t2026-04-23 17:18:20.87024 +0:00\n","type":"TABLE"}],"taskStatus":"SUCCESS","forms":"[]","status":"SUCCESS"},"sizeX":0,"hideCode":false,"width":12,"hideResult":false,"dynamicFormParams":"{}","row":0,"hasTitle":true,"hideVizConfig":false,"hideGutter":true,"relations":[],"forms":"[]"},{"col":0,"visualizationConfig":null,"hideInIFrame":false,"selectedVisualization":"table","title":"View Team History","message":["%sql","","-- View the team history","SELECT","    * ","FROM ","    USER_AI_AGENT_TEAM_HISTORY","ORDER BY","    START_DATE DESC"],"enabled":true,"result":{"startTime":1776967159699,"interpreter":"sql.medium","endTime":1776967160070,"results":[{"message":"TEAM_EXEC_ID\tTEAM_NAME\tSTATE\tSTART_DATE\tEND_DATE\tCONVERSATION_ID\n5025368E-C5BE-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\tOPS_ISSUES_SOLUTION_TEAM\tSUCCEEDED\t2026-04-23 17:57:43.577782 UTC\t2026-04-23 17:58:19.388073 +0:00\t5025368E-C5BD-4457-E063-6A13000AAF03\n50249D1C-B6C0-6781-E063-6A13000AF668\tRETURN_AGENCY_TEAM\tSUCCEEDED\t2026-04-23 17:17:29.146111 UTC\t2026-04-23 17:18:20.903307 +0:00\t50249D1C-B6BF-6781-E063-6A13000AF668\n","type":"TABLE"}],"taskStatus":"SUCCESS","forms":"[]","status":"SUCCESS"},"sizeX":0,"hideCode":false,"width":12,"hideResult":false,"dynamicFormParams":"{}","row":0,"hasTitle":true,"hideVizConfig":false,"hideGutter":true,"relations":[],"forms":"[]"},{"col":0,"visualizationConfig":null,"hideInIFrame":false,"selectedVisualization":"html","title":null,"message":["%md ","<center><h2 style='color:#0873d1'> End of Notebook <h2><\/center>"],"enabled":true,"result":{"startTime":1770584074331,"interpreter":"md.medium","endTime":1770584074704,"results":[{"message":"<center><h2 style='color:#0873d1'> End of Notebook <h2><\/center>\n","type":"HTML"}],"taskStatus":"SUCCESS","forms